[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 644 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Sat 18 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [abridged, edited]
http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-07/18/c_81111.htm


On 17 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 18 Jul 2020):
- 22 new cases of confirmed infections (6 imported cases: 3 in Guangdong province, 2 in Shandong province, 1 in Fujian province) and 16 locally transmitted cases in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region, 1 new case of suspected infection (locally transmitted case in Xinjiang), and no deaths.
- A total of 2004 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 644 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 758 recovered and discharged from hospital; 768 470 close contacts with infected patients; and 4072 are under medical observation.
- 14 new asymptomatic cases (including 5 imported); no asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 109 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 77 imported cases).
- 1713 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 58 cases since 16 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau.

