communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[There were 22 new confirmed cases in the past 24 hours -- 6 were imported and 16 were locally acquired in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region. While it is now 12 days with no new cases reported from Beijing, it appears another cluster is underway in Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region. According to another media report, the area will do massive testing. Also, 6 of the reported infections have symptoms and 11 are currently asymptomatic (there was 1 case confirmed yesterday according to the national Health Commission report for 16 Jul 2020; https://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1194880.shtml).

There were 14 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals (5 imported) and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, China has reported 37 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infection.

Hong Kong reported 58 new cases. The newly reported cases involve 24 males and 34 females aged between 6 and 92 years. Among them, 8 had travel history during the incubation period. One of the newly confirmed cases came from a residential care home for the elderly, and 2 additional cases were staff from the facility (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/17/P2020071700861.htm). Travel locations included India (2), Pakistan (2), Philippines (2), Ethiopia (1), and Malaysia (1). Details on the epidemiologic investigations are available at https://gia.info.gov.hk/general/202007/17/P2020071700861_346027_1_1594995150847.pdf.

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2. Hong Kong is dealing with increased local transmission associated with the lifting of restrictions; new severe restrictions have been announced.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7587301,155. - Mod.MPP]

