[In the past 24 hours, according to the report at the source URL, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 39 cases with 1 new death, compared with 60 cases and 2 new deaths in the previous day (16 Jul 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 95 consecutive days. There were 11 locally transmitted cases: Seoul (6), Gyeonggi (2), Incheon (1), Ulsan (1) and Jeju (1); and 28 imported cases: airport quarantine (12), Gyeonggi (8), Dae-gu (3), Gyeongnam (2), Busan (1), Incheon (1), and Jeonnam (1). There were 8 provinces reporting no newly confirmed cases (compared with 11 provinces yesterday, 16 Jul 2020).

Detailed updates on the 60 cases reported yesterday (16 Jul 2020) including information on clusters can be found in notices 439 and 440, and updated analyses including the 39 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours can be found in notice 441 at https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=&bid=0030.

The overall impression hasn't changed. Lifting of measures has been accompanied by increases in locally acquired infections through increasing clusters related to gatherings of people at employment (bringing it outside employment to contacts) and in houses of worship, and bars and clubs. However, that being said, importations are also playing a major role in the country as well. With the increase in cases, in the past few days there have been increases in reported deaths.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7587301,195. - Mod.MPP]

