[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is up by +233 cases and +11 deaths in the past 24 hours. The previous day's (16 Jul 2020) 24-hour change was +230 cases and +20 deaths. The numbers of hospitalized cases increased slightly, but cases in intensive care units are still in a slow decline.

Cases still continue to be concentrated in Lombardy, Veneto and Emilia-Romagna, the main provinces at the original epicenter of the outbreak (see tables at the link on the source URL to "download the latest data"). The provinces reporting the largest numbers of newly confirmed cases in the 24-hour period are Lombardy (55), Veneto (55) and Emilia-Romagna (54); Lazio (14) and Campania (12) are the other provinces reporting 10 or more cases. A total of 16 provinces reported fewer than 10 newly confirmed cases (5 provinces reported no new cases). Italy is now 72 days post phase 2 initial opening up and 56 days post 2nd stage of phase 2 opening up. For more detailed information on the outbreak, I suggest going to the source URL above.

Interpretation: So far so good, but there are periodic signs of localized increased transmission.... Time will tell.

A map of Italy showing regions can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/italy/regions.html and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7587301,75. - Mod.MPP]

