[D] Iran: 269 440 total cases, 13 791 deaths
Date: Fri 17 Jul 2020 15:34 IRDT
Source: Tasnim [edited]
https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/07/17/2308488/coronavirus-cases-in-iran-nearing-270-000


Speaking at a press conference on Friday [17 Jul 2020], Sima Sadat Lari said the total number of people tested positive for COVID-19 in Iran has risen to 269 440 following the detection of 2379 new cases since yesterday [16 Jul 2020].

Of the new cases detected over the past 24 hours, 1852 patients have been admitted to the hospital, she added. At least 232 873 patients have recovered from the coronavirus infection so far or have been discharged from hospitals across Iran, the spokeswoman said. She further put the death toll from COVID-19 in Iran at 13 791, saying the disease has taken the lives of 183 patients over the past 24 hours.

Among those undergoing treatment in medical centers at present, 3509 coronavirus patients have critical health conditions because of more severe infection, Lari noted. The spokeswoman also said more than 2 098 000 coronavirus diagnostic tests have been carried out in Iran so far.

--
