communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:

- The Americas region reported 58.0% of the global newly reported cases and 62.5% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period, maintaining its dominance as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 7 million cases. The USA reported 48.7% (67 165) of the newly confirmed cases in the region, and Brazil reported 28.5% (39 924), Mexico 4.5% (6149), Colombia 3.8% (5271), Peru 2.8% (3857), Argentina 3.1% (4250), and Chile 1.8% (2493).

- The European region reported 9.1% of the global newly reported cases and 8.4% of the newly confirmed deaths globally. Russia reported 29.5% (6406) of the regional newly confirmed cases, followed by Israel 8.7% (1896), Kazakhstan 7.9% (1707), Spain 6.3% (1361), Turkey 4.3% (933), Ukraine 3.7% (809), Romania 3.6% (777), the UK 3.0% (641), Kyrgyzstan 2.8% (603), Germany 2.7% (583), Azerbaijan 2.3% (493), Armenia 2.0% (442), and Uzbekistan 2.6% (562).

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.3% of the global newly reported cases and 8.9% of global newly reported fatalities. Saudi Arabia reported 18.3% (2764) of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Iran 16.6% (2500), Pakistan 13.8% (2085), Iraq 15.1% (2281), Oman 8.8% (1327), Egypt 6.2% (928), Kuwait 5.2% (791), Bahrain 3.5% (524), and Qatar 3.3% (494).

- The African region reported 8.3% of the global newly reported cases and 5.5% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 66.8% (13 172) of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Equatorial Guinea 6.6% (1307), Ghana 3.5% (695), Nigeria 3.0% (595), Algeria 3.0% (585), and Kenya 2.1% (421).

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.6% of the global newly reported cases and 0.58% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 65.1% (2416) of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Japan 15.7% (583), Australia 8.5% (315), Singapore 6.7% (248), China 2.1% (78), and South Korea 1.6% (60).

- The South East Asia region reported 16.6% of the global newly reported cases and 14.1% of global deaths. India reported 88.5% (34 956) of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 6.9% (2733) and Indonesia 4.0% (1574).

Impression: The overall picture is basically the same. The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis, followed by the South East Asia region, then Europe followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific representing the lowest daily caseload of all of the regions. The progression has been the initial "surge" in the Western Pacific region, followed by the surge in the European region and its decline, the entry and surging of the Americas region without any decrease, and the gradual and persistent increase in the South East Asia region, the increase then plateauing of the Eastern Mediterranean region, and the slow but steady increase in the Africa region and a slight increase in the Western Pacific region today.

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 17 Jul 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. - Mod.MPP]

